# Copy to .env and fill in (never commit .env)
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=
VITE_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=

# Optional: enables the internal /test page (password is still embedded in the client bundle if set)
# VITE_TEST_PAGE_PASSWORD=

# Google Drive → Credit Guardian (ingest-drive-clients):
# DRIVE_FOLDER_ID — root folder id or full share link (subfolders = clients).
# Google_Cloud_Key — Drive API key with access to that folder.
# DRIVE_CREDIT_ROOT_IS_DEDICATED — set true/1 when DRIVE_FOLDER_ID is ONLY credit clients (subfolder names
#   like "Zeus" / "Jabril" without the word "CREDIT"). If false (default), subfolder names must contain "CREDIT".
# DRIVE_CLIENT_FOLDER_ALIASES_JSON — optional. Maps chat names to Drive folder names, e.g. {"jabril":"zeus"}
#   (ingest-drive-clients). Use when the folder is "Zeus" but the user says "Jabril".
#
# Credit AI retrieval (optional — no DB tables; orchestration only):
# CREDIT_RETRIEVAL_URL — POST { task, intentSummary, caseStateSummary, maxItems } → JSON { disputeExamples, analysisPatterns, violationLogic } (arrays of strings). Empty arrays if unknown.
# CREDIT_RETRIEVAL_INLINE_JSON — dev-only same JSON shape (bypasses HTTP).
#
# Supabase Edge Function secrets (Dashboard → Project Settings → Edge Functions, or `supabase secrets set`):
# TELEGRAM_WEBHOOK_SECRET_TOKEN — high-entropy value (e.g. 64 hex); must match setWebhook secret_token; NOT the bot token.
# TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID — allowlisted Telegram chat id (string) for Control Center bot traffic.
# TELEGRAM_WEBHOOK_DEBUG_LOG — optional; set to 1 to log up to 80 chars of message text for webhook debugging (avoid in production).
